00:19:06,290 --> 00:19:11,554
And so, for example, for what the guide might look like,

449
00:19:12,732 --> 00:19:14,313
This is a screen cap of the guide.

450
00:19:14,373 --> 00:19:16,014
That's why the points are a different color,

451
00:19:16,074 --> 00:19:18,114
is that this is literally the webpage, or piece of it.

452
00:19:18,915 --> 00:19:21,576
It tells you, this is the manual itself,

453
00:19:21,656 --> 00:19:23,437
and all the manuals are text-based

454
00:19:23,917 --> 00:19:25,257
per game that's on the site,

455
00:19:25,818 --> 00:19:27,838
and it tells you with no pictures

456
00:19:28,819 --> 00:19:32,160
exactly what each button is and what it does.

457
00:19:33,647 --> 00:19:36,328
So you can use that then to communicate back.

458
00:19:36,989 --> 00:19:38,170
Avoid tables.

459
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:40,611
If you nest tables incorrectly

460
00:19:41,011 --> 00:19:42,532
or try to do variable lengths,

461
00:19:43,153 --> 00:19:44,374
it can mess up screen readers.

462
00:19:45,114 --> 00:19:45,835
Avoid tables.

463
00:19:46,735 --> 00:19:48,977
This is why we have the colons in the format here.

464
00:19:49,397 --> 00:19:50,758
It is possible to make a table

465
00:19:50,778 --> 00:19:52,039
that works well with screen readers.

466
00:19:52,519 --> 00:19:54,040
It's also very easy to make a mistake.

467
00:19:54,922 --> 00:19:57,503
So until you get that down, avoid tables.

468
00:19:58,103 --> 00:20:00,684
Also make sure you turn on Windows narrator

469
00:20:00,784 --> 00:20:02,505
or voiceover if you're using Apple,

470
00:20:02,965 --> 00:20:03,825
because if you do that,

471
00:20:03,865 --> 00:20:06,686
you can hear what your webpage sounds like,

472
00:20:07,126 --> 00:20:09,227
and you can find out what you have to do

473
00:20:09,607 --> 00:20:11,268
to make it sound the way you want it to.

474
00:20:12,489 --> 00:20:13,469
So it's important to test.

